WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:02.594
Subtitles by explosiveskull

00:02.597 --> 00:04.698
(BEES BUZZING)

00:04.700 --> 00:07.635
(WHIMSICAL MUSIC)

00:11.907 --> 00:16.479
(EVERYONE SINGING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

00:18.781 --> 00:22.618
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

00:32.095 --> 00:35.397
(EVERYONE SINGING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

00:35.399 --> 00:39.203
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

00:49.080 --> 00:52.314
(EVERYONE SINGING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

00:52.316 --> 00:56.120
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

00:58.089 --> 00:59.254
Tatiana!

00:59.256 --> 01:00.823
Excuse me, sorry.

01:00.825 --> 01:02.024
Tatiana?

01:02.026 --> 01:03.659
Oh, Mr. Wayne, how
charming, you found me.

01:03.661 --> 01:05.861
I'm desperately searching
for Honey, have you seen her?

01:05.863 --> 01:07.029
Pardon?

01:07.031 --> 01:08.498
I'm looking for Honey,
have you seen her?

01:08.500 --> 01:09.466
Honey?

01:09.468 --> 01:10.699
Yes.

01:10.701 --> 01:11.633
I don't know where she
is, come on, join in.

01:11.635 --> 01:12.901
No, I can't, thank you.

01:12.903 --> 01:14.304
Oh come you rascal,
jump in the conga line

01:14.306 --> 01:15.872
and debauch for eternity.

01:15.874 --> 01:17.006
I'm alright.

01:17.008 --> 01:19.842
Oh come on
handsome, loosen up.

01:19.844 --> 01:24.584
(PERFORMER SINGING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:28.287 --> 01:29.155
[SHOEROPE] Honey?

01:31.290 --> 01:32.124
Honey!

01:37.762 --> 01:41.100
(PUNCHING AND GRUNTING)

01:46.873 --> 01:49.775
(SOFT JAZZY THEME)

02:00.621 --> 02:03.690
(SOFT DRAMATIC THEME)

02:19.706 --> 02:21.107
You called Madam?

02:21.109 --> 02:22.643
[HONEY] Brilliant.

02:22.645 --> 02:24.410
You're the perfect size.

02:24.412 --> 02:25.246
Good.

02:26.648 --> 02:28.981
I'm at a loss at detecting
what you mean exactly.

02:28.983 --> 02:33.120
[HONEY] That is your
profession sir, to detect.

02:33.122 --> 02:34.288
I have my moments.

02:34.290 --> 02:36.523
We all have our moments.

02:36.525 --> 02:38.593
The art lies in making
a habit of them.

02:40.262 --> 02:41.096
Call me honey.

02:42.565 --> 02:43.666
How do you do Honey?

02:45.535 --> 02:46.670
Inspector Shoerope.

02:48.237 --> 02:49.038
Yes.

02:50.573 --> 02:54.074
You have some catching up
to do Inspector Shoerope.

02:54.076 --> 02:55.642
Champagne?

02:55.644 --> 02:58.682
Oh, thank you but I refrain
from the liquor when on duty.

02:59.583 --> 03:00.881
Fuck that.

03:00.883 --> 03:02.818
I'm yet to start your
industrial clock.

03:05.322 --> 03:06.156
Go on.

03:07.157 --> 03:08.088
If you insist.

03:08.090 --> 03:10.227
Never insist, always persist.

03:14.097 --> 03:14.930
So what am I?

03:16.634 --> 03:18.233
I'm sorry?

03:18.235 --> 03:20.103
For my Hallow's
Eve costume party.

03:23.174 --> 03:25.742
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

03:29.413 --> 03:33.483
Welcome, you ghastly
ghouls of Hallow's Eve,

03:33.485 --> 03:35.584
to the annual costume contest.

03:35.586 --> 03:38.589
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

03:39.625 --> 03:41.790
You know what time it is.

03:41.792 --> 03:45.095
I hereby announce, commence.

03:45.097 --> 03:47.863
If I call your name
you are a nominee,

03:47.865 --> 03:50.966
saunter your suave self
onto this very stage

03:50.968 --> 03:55.004
and have a fine boogie-woogie
with yours truly.

03:55.006 --> 03:58.108
You are invited.

03:58.110 --> 03:59.578
Your nominees are,

04:01.013 --> 04:02.579
Candy.

04:02.581 --> 04:06.918
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

04:09.522 --> 04:11.455
Mr. Fairweather.

04:11.457 --> 04:15.795
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

04:17.730 --> 04:18.897
Mr. Allbright.

04:20.065 --> 04:24.203
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

04:27.039 --> 04:28.473
Honey.

04:28.475 --> 04:32.812
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

04:36.049 --> 04:36.883
Kitty.

04:38.117 --> 04:40.919
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

04:40.921 --> 04:45.658
And last but by no
means least, Mr. Wayne.

04:45.660 --> 04:48.729
(APPLAUDING CEASING)

04:51.333 --> 04:52.799
Right.

04:52.801 --> 04:54.299
Please don't tell me
you're completely unaware.

04:54.301 --> 04:56.068
[SHOEROPE] I'm afraid so.

04:56.070 --> 04:56.904
Huh.

04:57.739 --> 04:58.573
Shame.

04:59.674 --> 05:00.508
Here.

05:02.142 --> 05:04.646
(SOFT MUSIC)

05:08.450 --> 05:09.284
A bee.

05:10.185 --> 05:11.019
Correct.

05:14.422 --> 05:17.725
You really should place
Hallow's Eve in your calendar.

05:17.727 --> 05:19.294
It's such a marvelous occasion.

05:20.362 --> 05:22.864
(JAZZY THEME)

05:24.333 --> 05:26.000
It's also my birthday.

05:27.068 --> 05:28.635
Why,

05:28.637 --> 05:30.239
many happy returns.

05:32.274 --> 05:34.845
(EERIE MUSIC)

05:37.046 --> 05:38.512
Aren't you going
to ask my age?

05:38.514 --> 05:39.583
Gentlemen never do.

05:41.351 --> 05:42.952
Ladies never tell.

05:45.322 --> 05:47.856
I have an entire room
filled with costumes

05:47.858 --> 05:50.159
Inspector Shoerope,
a vast collection,

05:51.596 --> 05:53.330
for to feast your eyes.

05:54.731 --> 05:59.401
Everything from cowboys to
Indians to pirates to sailors,

05:59.403 --> 06:02.837
to kings, to queens,

06:02.839 --> 06:05.374
to cops, to robbers.

06:05.376 --> 06:09.714
But for you, I know exactly
what your get-up should be.

06:12.216 --> 06:13.217
I'm in your hands.

06:15.253 --> 06:16.087
Like I said,

06:18.790 --> 06:20.625
it will fit perfectly.

06:24.630 --> 06:27.566
You're the same
size, you and my...

06:30.134 --> 06:33.372
(DRAMATIC THEME MUSIC)

06:36.341 --> 06:38.844
(SOFT MUSIC)

06:39.945 --> 06:42.612
You were the same size.

06:42.614 --> 06:46.553
("IN THE MOOD" BY GLEN MILLER)

06:55.795 --> 06:58.129
It was precisely as this
we entered the dance floor

06:58.131 --> 07:00.865
only a year ago,
my husband and I.

07:00.867 --> 07:04.736
We held hands like so, you
and me, this very second.

07:04.738 --> 07:08.908
(PEOPLE CHEERING AND CHATTERING)

07:14.280 --> 07:17.485
Although where I am
utterly disappointed,

07:18.819 --> 07:22.354
is my husband was consuming
liquor far quicker.

07:22.356 --> 07:25.089
As I spoke upon my arrival,
mixing business with pleasure

07:25.091 --> 07:26.391
is against my code of conduct.

07:26.393 --> 07:29.628
Well change your code
with gusto dear sir.

07:29.630 --> 07:32.700
It is I conducing your
cherished conduct after all.

07:34.068 --> 07:35.935
You must spend your
evening exactly as my dear

07:35.937 --> 07:38.103
deceased husband spent
his because then,

07:38.105 --> 07:40.874
and only then, can
you detect the truth.

07:40.876 --> 07:44.142
Conveniently at this juncture
we separated upon my saying,

07:44.144 --> 07:47.847
run along darling and obtain
yourself another drink.

07:47.849 --> 07:49.618
You know I like my men wet.

07:51.521 --> 07:55.457
("IN THE MOOD" BY GLEN MILLER)

07:57.527 --> 08:00.596
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

08:04.133 --> 08:06.199
Excuse me, there we go.

08:06.201 --> 08:07.503
I say, cheeky.

08:08.638 --> 08:11.171
A mightily strong touch
you possess Sheriff.

08:11.173 --> 08:12.806
Apologies Madam,
I'm attempting my way

08:12.808 --> 08:14.040
into the bar is all.

08:14.042 --> 08:16.277
That is most certainly
not all, the two of us

08:16.279 --> 08:19.079
bar-bound now sir, take my hand,

08:19.081 --> 08:20.548
lead me to the watering-hole.

08:20.550 --> 08:22.017
I'm really just trying
to sneak on through, Madam.

08:22.019 --> 08:25.386
Sneak for two damn you, I
insist, with a vigorous thirst.

08:25.388 --> 08:27.322
Certainly, ah, Mr. Wayne.

08:27.324 --> 08:30.458
Tatiana, thoughts on my
costume please Mr. Wayne?

08:30.460 --> 08:31.393
[SHOEROPE] Grand.

08:31.395 --> 08:32.626
Thank you, I'm a Gazelle.

08:32.629 --> 08:33.629
Huh, delightful

08:33.631 --> 08:35.363
Last year, I was a rhinoceros.

08:35.365 --> 08:36.498
Very impressive.

08:36.500 --> 08:39.437
And the year
before that, a hippo.

08:49.580 --> 08:51.082
Very fucking impressive.

08:52.317 --> 08:54.550
The idles of a
wasted war-time youth.

08:54.552 --> 08:57.688
Not wasted on me, my knees
most certainly went idle.

08:57.690 --> 08:59.221
Is it loaded?

08:59.223 --> 09:02.592
I have replaced the costume
revolver with my own, so yes.

09:02.594 --> 09:04.962
I can tell Sheriff.

09:04.964 --> 09:06.197
May I ask you a question?

09:14.039 --> 09:15.238
You don't think I should have
been a French maid, do you?

09:15.240 --> 09:17.507
No I consider your
bee splendidly special.

09:17.509 --> 09:19.710
Really, truly?

09:19.712 --> 09:21.211
I'm so perfectly
spoiled for choice, see.

09:21.213 --> 09:22.412
[SHOEROPE] I can.

09:22.414 --> 09:24.414
I do so love to
throw a costume party.

09:24.416 --> 09:25.248
It would seem.

09:25.250 --> 09:26.416
Any excuse.

09:26.418 --> 09:27.685
I haven't the pleasure
of attending many.

09:27.687 --> 09:29.821
It is my absolute
favorite avocation.

09:29.823 --> 09:31.121
They do have a certain charm.

09:31.123 --> 09:31.956
[HONEY] Precisely.

09:31.958 --> 09:33.191
[SHOEROPE] And magic.

09:33.193 --> 09:34.125
But the trials
and tribulations...

09:34.127 --> 09:35.059
Of those I am familiar.

09:35.061 --> 09:36.126
Of making up one's own mind.

09:36.128 --> 09:36.961
[SHOEROPE] Honey?

09:36.963 --> 09:38.428
Yes,

09:38.430 --> 09:39.932
Inspector Shoerope?

09:39.934 --> 09:42.500
I'm reluctant to slice such
a moment of contemplation

09:42.502 --> 09:45.704
and deliberation but it's my
professional prerogative, nay,

09:45.706 --> 09:47.605
duty, nay, requirement,

09:47.607 --> 09:49.207
to understand what it is exactly

09:49.209 --> 09:50.541
for which you
summoned my services.

09:50.543 --> 09:51.946
I thought you'd never ask.

09:53.881 --> 09:57.485
One can't be too careful on
this most haunted of evenings.

10:01.756 --> 10:03.959
Prying ears everywhere, you see.

10:04.960 --> 10:07.094
And wandering eyes aplenty.

10:16.138 --> 10:19.605
I'm sure you're often thrust
into tragic circumstances,

10:19.607 --> 10:21.241
a man of your profession,
but this one does carry

10:21.243 --> 10:22.609
a certain particular jeopardy.

10:22.611 --> 10:23.476
Tragedy most certainly is a...

10:23.478 --> 10:25.444
I'm not finished, sir.

10:25.446 --> 10:26.682
Not in the slightest.

10:27.817 --> 10:30.183
You see, exactly
one year ago today,

10:30.185 --> 10:33.956
on this very evening,
and in this very home,

10:35.958 --> 10:37.559
my husband was
brutally murdered.

10:38.860 --> 10:39.662
Gosh.

10:41.296 --> 10:43.363
I'd heard snippets of such a
crime from my new colleagues

10:43.365 --> 10:44.564
in the station but
hadn't the chance to put

10:44.566 --> 10:45.800
two and two together.

10:45.802 --> 10:47.301
Well said, colleagues
were success-less

10:47.303 --> 10:50.370
in their pursuit of the
truth, without imagination.

10:50.372 --> 10:52.941
[SHOEROPE] Imagination is a
gift received all too seldom.

10:52.943 --> 10:53.743
Quite.

10:55.478 --> 10:57.713
And solving a crime requires
more than just dotting

10:57.715 --> 10:59.815
the Is and crossing the Ts.

10:59.817 --> 11:01.315
This is true.

11:01.317 --> 11:02.783
Tell me, how long have you
wielded the weight of justice?

11:02.785 --> 11:04.152
Three weeks, Honey.

11:04.154 --> 11:05.754
(LAUGHING)

11:05.756 --> 11:08.025
My, we've not a
second more to spare.

11:10.994 --> 11:12.561
I've relentlessly ensured
that every party guest

11:12.563 --> 11:13.528
who was in attendance last year

11:13.530 --> 11:14.763
is again present this evening.

11:14.765 --> 11:17.166
Look, I sent out
invitations from the

11:17.168 --> 11:19.768
identical address book,
painstakingly received

11:19.770 --> 11:22.237
and cross-referenced all RSVPs.

11:22.239 --> 11:24.239
And tonight, upon cocktail hour,

11:24.241 --> 11:26.641
I stood at our entrance
as a permanent fixture,

11:26.643 --> 11:28.711
striking off names
without exception

11:28.713 --> 11:31.750
as each respective
individual arrived.

11:35.286 --> 11:37.319
Along with a perfectly
pleasant greeting of course.

11:37.321 --> 11:38.788
Naturally.

11:38.790 --> 11:40.256
So the fucker who
murdered my husband

11:40.258 --> 11:41.758
on this very evening only
a year ago must again

11:41.760 --> 11:42.825
be present tonight.

11:42.827 --> 11:44.228
I see.

11:44.230 --> 11:45.429
And what of the staff?

11:45.431 --> 11:47.698
♪ Whoa

11:47.700 --> 11:49.365
♪ This is

11:49.367 --> 11:51.468
♪ The happy house

11:51.470 --> 11:54.339
♪ We're happy here

11:56.041 --> 11:57.641
In five more years, I'll
have been all of the animals

11:57.643 --> 11:59.376
in a Kenyan safari.

11:59.378 --> 12:00.878
What were you last year?

12:00.880 --> 12:01.879
I wasn't here.

12:01.881 --> 12:03.681
You don't say?

12:03.683 --> 12:05.783
Fresh meat.

12:05.785 --> 12:08.285
You're fortunate
gazelles are herbivores.

12:08.287 --> 12:12.190
For you however, I
might make an exception.

12:12.192 --> 12:14.491
Don't fracture the food
chain on my behalf, please.

12:14.493 --> 12:15.960
What would you like?

12:15.962 --> 12:17.996
Champagne with a twist of
champagne, please and thank you.

12:17.998 --> 12:19.232
Champagne and a scotch.

12:20.566 --> 12:23.368
You're awfully brave
wearing this sheriff costume.

12:23.370 --> 12:24.836
Brave?

12:24.838 --> 12:27.440
Why yes, considering
the tragedy of a year ago.

12:28.341 --> 12:29.808
The murder you mean?

12:29.810 --> 12:31.643
Precisely, and the fact
that the victim was...

12:31.645 --> 12:34.046
(LOUD SUCKING)

12:34.048 --> 12:34.914
Uh!

12:34.916 --> 12:35.750
Bang!

12:37.185 --> 12:38.983
It wasn't me Sheriff,
I didn't do it,

12:38.985 --> 12:41.921
you've got the wrong
man, by golly you have.

12:41.923 --> 12:44.357
Quite the costume
sir, Mr. Conick.

12:45.860 --> 12:47.726
Thank you, Wayne.

12:47.728 --> 12:48.994
Mr. Wayne.

12:48.996 --> 12:51.530
You may so disclose
your ponderings on mine.

12:51.532 --> 12:53.033
Truly something.

12:53.035 --> 12:54.234
I'm Sherlock Holmes.

12:54.236 --> 12:55.469
Yes, you are.

12:56.938 --> 13:00.774
Ooh, excellent choice
my man, scotch me up too.

13:00.776 --> 13:03.777
Oh and I see you're
lubricating the cheeky gazelle.

13:03.779 --> 13:06.246
Stop it Mr. Conick, you
must set a good example.

13:06.248 --> 13:07.848
This is Mr. Wayne's
first year here.

13:07.850 --> 13:12.853
Oh well, aren't you the
needle in the haystack.

13:12.855 --> 13:16.090
Allow me to welcome you to our
wonderful Hallow's Eve bash.

13:16.092 --> 13:17.624
Our?

13:17.626 --> 13:20.261
Mr. Conick is something of a
celebrity around these parts.

13:20.263 --> 13:22.063
It's an honor to
claim your company sir.

13:22.065 --> 13:24.065
Oh my family simply
shares close ties

13:24.067 --> 13:25.599
with the local land is all.

13:25.601 --> 13:27.602
Close ties, meaning they
have all the land tied up.

13:27.604 --> 13:30.538
Don't let our dear
friend's modesty fool you.

13:30.540 --> 13:31.973
If you're looking to
purchase a regional property,

13:31.975 --> 13:34.475
this man's family
shall seal the deal.

13:34.477 --> 13:36.546
We are in Conick-on-Marsh
after all.

13:38.147 --> 13:42.552
("WHAT A WASTER"
BY THE LIBERTINES")

13:43.853 --> 13:44.819
♪ What a waster

13:44.821 --> 13:46.221
♪ What a fucking waster

13:46.223 --> 13:47.856
♪ You pissed it
all up the wall ♪

13:47.858 --> 13:49.157
♪ Round the corner

13:49.159 --> 13:52.694
♪ Where they chased her
there's tears coming ♪

13:52.696 --> 13:55.731
I'm in awe of your unique
efforts Honey, really,

13:55.733 --> 13:56.932
but one can never
recreate what has

13:56.934 --> 13:58.368
passed with complete sincerity.

13:58.370 --> 14:01.003
There is always the possibility,
if not inevitability

14:01.005 --> 14:03.373
of a fleeting fancy throwing
a spanner in the works.

14:03.375 --> 14:05.277
Keep your fancy
spanner sheathed.

14:06.111 --> 14:08.545
As it was, as it is.

14:12.384 --> 14:14.685
All that's divergent
is my broken heart.

14:16.521 --> 14:18.256
Last year it was
very much whole.

14:19.491 --> 14:20.823
You have my
undying compassion.

14:20.825 --> 14:23.027
Oh spare me your sympathy.

14:23.029 --> 14:24.363
Feelings are for the frail.

14:29.368 --> 14:31.037
And the frail alone.

14:32.071 --> 14:34.204
I'm right in assuming that,

14:34.206 --> 14:35.940
should I accept
this investigation,

14:35.942 --> 14:38.441
we would be in cahoots in my
insisting none of the guests

14:38.443 --> 14:40.211
discover my true identity.

14:40.213 --> 14:41.812
Go on.

14:41.814 --> 14:44.915
It would compromise the
covert nature of my inquiry.

14:44.917 --> 14:47.020
I would consider calling
myself a certain,

14:48.821 --> 14:49.655
Mr. Wayne.

14:51.892 --> 14:53.657
And all those who
pry shall receive

14:53.659 --> 14:56.462
our agreed decoy
answer, Mr. Wayne.

14:59.132 --> 15:02.633
You are my chaperone, with
whom I intend to conclude

15:02.635 --> 15:04.905
the evening in the height
of passion, concur?

15:08.275 --> 15:09.110
As you wish.

15:11.511 --> 15:12.347
Settled then.

15:14.382 --> 15:16.884
Come, come, time
waits for no man.

15:19.619 --> 15:21.821
Oh, stop it Tatiana,
you'll inflate even the most

15:21.823 --> 15:24.522
viscous of egos
with such flattery.

15:24.524 --> 15:27.127
Not quite any property
you understand Mr. Wayne,

15:27.129 --> 15:30.096
despite my incessant advances,
our magnificent venue

15:30.098 --> 15:33.200
for this evening remains very
much in the tenacious hands

15:33.202 --> 15:35.534
of the charmingly
nouveau Ms. Honey.

15:35.536 --> 15:36.372
Indeed.

15:39.174 --> 15:41.341
I am content with my current
abode but should my wings

15:41.343 --> 15:43.576
grow restless, I'll flap
them in your direction.

15:43.578 --> 15:46.247
When the soaring skies
beckon, a Conick nest, thatched,

15:46.249 --> 15:47.716
swept and dressed awaits.

15:49.318 --> 15:52.786
Here, I'm certain I've seen
your costume before old boy.

15:52.788 --> 15:55.822
Yes, I'm sure, the shop-teller
from whom I'm purchased it

15:55.824 --> 15:59.260
just yesterday advised it was
a particularly potent pick.

15:59.262 --> 16:00.761
Apparently so.

16:00.763 --> 16:01.695
Wonderfully authentic.

16:01.697 --> 16:03.831
Hmm, wonderfully damning too.

16:03.833 --> 16:04.766
Tatiana don't.

16:04.768 --> 16:05.599
He knows.

16:05.601 --> 16:06.533
[SHOEROPE] Knows what.

16:06.535 --> 16:07.335
[CONICK] Enough please.

16:07.337 --> 16:08.568
About Honey's husband.

16:08.570 --> 16:09.804
- Really, come on.
- Oh, I do yes.

16:09.806 --> 16:10.738
A right royal
miserable subject.

16:10.740 --> 16:11.973
[SHOEROPE] And what of it?

16:11.975 --> 16:12.940
Let's hope you
have better luck.

16:12.942 --> 16:13.608
- Must we?
- Luck?

16:13.610 --> 16:14.242
[TATIANA] Yes.

16:14.244 --> 16:15.511
No.

16:15.513 --> 16:19.147
Ah, marvelous, allons-y
Tatiana, a dance is due.

16:19.149 --> 16:20.516
Well we can't leave
Mr. Wayne all alone.

16:20.518 --> 16:21.750
Oh, I'm quite
alright, thank you.

16:21.752 --> 16:24.119
What do you mean by all
this luck and bravery?

16:24.121 --> 16:25.787
Well honey's husband was
wearing a sheriff's costume

16:25.789 --> 16:27.256
when he was murdered of course.

16:27.258 --> 16:28.659
It's rather a cursed get-up.

16:30.061 --> 16:30.993
I see.

16:30.995 --> 16:31.927
[TATIANA] Don't fret though.

16:31.929 --> 16:33.430
Lightning seldom strikes twice.

16:33.432 --> 16:34.763
My feet are simply ravenous
for a lick of the jitterbug

16:34.765 --> 16:36.031
and I insist they be fed.

16:36.033 --> 16:37.535
A dear moment, golly.

16:38.969 --> 16:41.404
It's been a pleasure Mr. Wayne.

16:41.406 --> 16:44.139
[SHOEROPE] The pleasure
was all mine Tatiana.

16:44.141 --> 16:44.973
Mr. Conick.

16:44.975 --> 16:45.811
Good evening.

16:47.345 --> 16:50.515
(JAZZY MUSIC PLAYING)

16:54.820 --> 16:56.319
[SHOEROPE] Just borrowing you.

16:56.321 --> 16:57.254
[HONEY] Excuse
me for a moment,

16:57.256 --> 17:00.090
a dabble of fun, I assure you.

17:00.092 --> 17:02.626
(EERIE MUSIC)

17:04.297 --> 17:05.396
Whatever's the matter?

17:05.397 --> 17:06.930
Name your game.

17:06.932 --> 17:10.067
Oh, Inspector Shoerope, how
becoming and in such company.

17:10.069 --> 17:11.733
Why this costume?

17:11.736 --> 17:12.571
Sorry?

17:13.872 --> 17:17.541
The costume upon my
back, why this one?

17:17.544 --> 17:21.979
Um, well it's a perfect fit,
and quite magnificently apt.

17:21.981 --> 17:22.813
Oh yes?

17:22.815 --> 17:24.080
That we agreed.

17:24.083 --> 17:26.219
Your murdered
husband was a sheriff.

17:28.255 --> 17:30.857
(EERIE MUSIC)

17:34.161 --> 17:36.061
I did have an ulterior
motive for the marriage

17:36.063 --> 17:37.529
of body to costume, I confess.

17:37.531 --> 17:38.865
I'm listening.

17:41.835 --> 17:43.468
This was the exact garb
my husband was wearing

17:43.470 --> 17:45.038
upon his death only a year ago.

17:46.773 --> 17:47.609
They very same?

17:50.944 --> 17:52.345
Precisely.

17:52.347 --> 17:53.546
Oh no, Inspector Shoerope,
I've preserved it

17:53.548 --> 17:54.813
with such delicate
love and care,

17:54.815 --> 17:55.780
let not a moment of
heat set it alight.

17:55.782 --> 17:57.250
Love and care my foot.

17:57.252 --> 17:58.351
It's evidence if
you please, evidence.

17:58.353 --> 17:59.185
Precisely.

17:59.187 --> 18:00.019
[HONEY] Oh be careful.

18:00.021 --> 18:01.554
It's coming right off.

18:01.556 --> 18:02.522
Please don't do that.

18:02.524 --> 18:03.524
Absolute insanity.

18:03.526 --> 18:04.924
Stop, I beg you.

18:04.926 --> 18:06.259
It's a sordid idea.

18:06.261 --> 18:07.661
This is enough!

18:08.563 --> 18:11.833
(SOFT DRAMATIC THEME)

18:16.972 --> 18:19.807
I'm bewitched,
Inspector Shoerope.

18:21.042 --> 18:21.877
Bewitched.

18:23.612 --> 18:26.113
Upon my husband's final
exhalation I vowed that

18:26.115 --> 18:27.848
I would deliver his killer
to the unforgiving arms

18:27.850 --> 18:29.850
of justice and I am
eternally haunted until this

18:29.852 --> 18:30.686
I have done.

18:33.055 --> 18:34.955
I desperately assumed
that it would benefit

18:34.957 --> 18:36.558
your investigation and
therefore my bedeviled self

18:36.560 --> 18:40.794
if you looked and you
felt exactly as he did

18:40.796 --> 18:44.566
while trying to solve this most
muddled of murder mysteries.

18:44.568 --> 18:46.635
I am humbled to be
of assistance, Honey.

18:46.637 --> 18:48.336
I can't however
say I'm familiar,

18:48.338 --> 18:50.540
nor comfortable with
such methodology.

18:59.015 --> 19:02.750
Because a man only truly
understands another man

19:02.752 --> 19:06.123
when he's stepping in his
shoes, feeling what he felt,

19:07.458 --> 19:09.827
and possessing
what he possessed.

19:12.897 --> 19:16.000
You see, you can see here,

19:17.569 --> 19:21.872
the slight scarring from the
fatal wound upon the fabric.

19:24.610 --> 19:25.444
I do.

19:26.877 --> 19:31.383
I undertook the reparations
myself as a form of therapy

19:33.519 --> 19:37.954
but a kitchen knife
thrust with great force

19:37.956 --> 19:40.426
is a tedious mark
to erase entirely.

19:44.196 --> 19:45.365
And when I found him...

19:47.467 --> 19:48.568
What of it?

19:49.736 --> 19:52.805
The murder weapon
was still within,

19:54.173 --> 19:57.210
and blood cascaded
from the fatal wound.

20:02.515 --> 20:04.652
Any evidence from
the scene of the crime?

20:08.888 --> 20:12.493
The killer must have
been wearing gloves,

20:14.193 --> 20:17.131
for no fingerprints adorned
the handle of the blade.

20:18.532 --> 20:21.634
And countless hours spent
scouring the kitchen,

20:21.636 --> 20:24.036
for that's where his
life was terminated,

20:24.038 --> 20:26.705
proved futile in our attempts
to discover any slither

20:26.707 --> 20:28.675
of a clue at all.

20:28.677 --> 20:31.410
The work of a
seasoned hand, I'm sure.

20:31.412 --> 20:34.482
A seasoned hand that's
laid its cold touch

20:35.684 --> 20:38.218
on my pillow every night since.

20:40.622 --> 20:41.656
I drink to sleep,

20:45.059 --> 20:46.796
but the drink duly
fuels my tears.

20:49.097 --> 20:52.366
You have my
deepest sympathies.

20:52.368 --> 20:54.537
Spare me your
fucking sympathy.

20:56.271 --> 20:58.474
We've established you must.

21:01.377 --> 21:02.445
Tell me this.

21:04.613 --> 21:07.483
Have you ever experienced
the pain of parting by death?

21:10.152 --> 21:11.586
I have not.

21:11.588 --> 21:12.922
Of course not.

21:13.989 --> 21:15.258
So run along,

21:16.226 --> 21:17.059
Sheriff.

21:18.894 --> 21:20.363
You've a crime to solve.

21:22.966 --> 21:26.135
(HUNTING THEME MUSIC)

21:37.114 --> 21:40.785
("NIGHTMARE" BY ARTIE SHAW)

21:53.664 --> 21:57.803
(PEOPLE CHATTERING AND LAUGHING)

22:25.364 --> 22:27.500
I didn't foresee
spying you here Sheriff.

22:29.636 --> 22:30.835
Commissioner, my word!

22:30.837 --> 22:33.604
And my surprise is
not fused with pleasure.

22:33.606 --> 22:36.641
Name your purpose amongst
such illustrious company,

22:36.643 --> 22:37.941
Shoerope.

22:37.943 --> 22:39.611
I was called sir.

22:39.613 --> 22:40.746
By whom?

22:40.748 --> 22:42.280
Honey, sir.

22:42.282 --> 22:44.015
Finally lost her
marbles has she?

22:44.017 --> 22:46.652
In regards to the murder of
her husband a year ago, sir.

22:46.654 --> 22:48.720
Ah, and you flock like
a bee to the flower.

22:48.722 --> 22:49.987
I was on duty, sir.

22:49.989 --> 22:51.557
As a sheriff?

22:51.559 --> 22:53.425
She had me change into this
upon my arrival actually, sir.

22:53.427 --> 22:54.426
Did she?

22:54.428 --> 22:55.894
Darling?

22:55.896 --> 22:57.629
Darling, I've been searching
far and wide for you.

22:57.631 --> 23:01.133
Well done, you've
found me sweetheart.

23:01.135 --> 23:04.036
Meet Inspector Shoerope,
Inspector Shoerope, my wife.

23:04.038 --> 23:05.939
My, Inspector Shoerope,
you make out to be

23:05.941 --> 23:07.639
a superbly
swashbuckling sheriff.

23:07.641 --> 23:10.243
Thank you madam, you're
a marvelous mermaid.

23:10.245 --> 23:12.110
Ah, just a little
something I keep hidden

23:12.112 --> 23:15.047
in the back of my wardrobe
should such an occasion arise.

23:15.049 --> 23:15.982
Nothing really.

23:15.984 --> 23:16.916
Oh that's not true dearest,

23:16.918 --> 23:18.384
it's quite the prize possession.

23:18.386 --> 23:21.454
Stop Commissioner, a lady
never spares her secrets, silly.

23:21.456 --> 23:22.957
You're making me blush.

23:22.959 --> 23:23.756
Well, you can run that
little blush of yours off

23:23.758 --> 23:25.291
with a jaunt to the bar.

23:25.293 --> 23:27.795
I was rather hoping to catch
a stash of fresh air my love.

23:27.797 --> 23:31.164
It'll still be here when
you return, sugarplum.

23:31.166 --> 23:34.100
Shoerope and I
require two scotches.

23:34.102 --> 23:35.569
Of course.

23:35.571 --> 23:36.937
Inspector Shoerope.

23:36.939 --> 23:37.807
[SHOEROPE] Madam.

23:40.476 --> 23:43.913
Bothersome she may
sometimes be, but I love her.

23:45.716 --> 23:47.448
I'm Captain Hook, approve?

23:47.450 --> 23:48.949
I assumed sir, it's very good.

23:48.951 --> 23:51.620
Thank you, we decided on
a nautical theme this year.

23:51.622 --> 23:53.187
♪ Lover's rock

23:53.189 --> 23:57.359
♪ But woops there goes the
strength that you need ♪

23:57.361 --> 24:00.795
♪ To make real
cool lover's rock ♪

24:00.797 --> 24:04.566
♪ A genuine lover
takes off his clothes ♪

24:04.568 --> 24:06.133
♪ And he can make a lover in a

24:06.135 --> 24:08.570
Now, Shoerope, what
has she told you?

24:08.572 --> 24:09.371
Who, Sir?

24:09.373 --> 24:10.873
Honey, of the murder.

24:10.875 --> 24:12.807
Oh right, yes, quite a
fair amount actually sir.

24:12.809 --> 24:14.276
In fact you rather caught me
in a contemplative moment.

24:14.278 --> 24:15.912
Don't trust a word of it.

24:15.914 --> 24:17.112
Why ever not?

24:17.114 --> 24:18.580
I'm your ranking
officer, do as I say,

24:18.582 --> 24:19.748
not a single word she has
spoken nor shall speak

24:19.750 --> 24:21.684
with her maniacal
mouth is to be trusted.

24:21.686 --> 24:23.419
You promise me this?

24:23.421 --> 24:25.220
Well, I certainly have to
request that you explain your...

24:25.222 --> 24:27.623
[RUSSELL] OK, you
dirty rotten scoundrels.

24:27.625 --> 24:30.560
Slither yourselves to
the dance floor pronto,

24:30.562 --> 24:32.828
all to the dance floor at once.

24:32.830 --> 24:34.765
Huzzah, they're going to announce
the best costume winners

24:34.767 --> 24:36.265
and then they bob for apples,

24:36.267 --> 24:39.001
this is the most exciting part
and quite frankly dear boy,

24:39.003 --> 24:43.508
I fancy my chances this year.

24:46.378 --> 24:47.811
Well on your
toes now Mr. Wayne,

24:47.813 --> 24:49.980
we're all ready and waiting.

24:49.982 --> 24:54.320
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

24:55.688 --> 24:58.990
The nominees, you ghostly
fiends of the night,

24:58.992 --> 25:00.726
but wait, but wait,

25:01.594 --> 25:03.628
there can only be two winners.

25:03.630 --> 25:05.362
Two winners ladies
and gentlemen,

25:05.364 --> 25:07.232
one lady and one gentleman.

25:09.035 --> 25:11.836
(AUDIENCE HOOTING)

25:11.838 --> 25:13.172
Our lady champion is,

25:15.275 --> 25:17.909
our beautiful host, Honey.

25:17.911 --> 25:20.979
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

25:20.981 --> 25:23.483
Any words for your
thoroughly adoring fans?

25:31.224 --> 25:35.027
I'd like to thank you all
awfully from the very bottom

25:35.029 --> 25:36.063
of my heart.

25:37.965 --> 25:39.868
Such a wonderful Hallow's Eve.

25:43.404 --> 25:45.774
And I am sincerely
moved every year by

25:47.308 --> 25:49.677
each of yours
continued attendance.

25:53.615 --> 25:56.051
What an honor it is to be
your winner, thank you.

25:57.386 --> 25:58.618
(AUDIENCE CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

25:58.620 --> 26:01.089
The wonderful sweet
as they come, Honey.

26:02.289 --> 26:06.459
And don't you just
look sumptuous, huh?

26:06.461 --> 26:09.262
How ravishing, I could
eat you up for breakfast,

26:09.264 --> 26:10.731
lunch and dinner.

26:10.733 --> 26:12.165
(AUDIENCE HOOTING)

26:12.167 --> 26:14.002
Maybe a little bit
on the side, too.

26:15.571 --> 26:17.370
But who will be
the lucky gentleman

26:17.372 --> 26:22.077
joining our beautiful
lady, who will it be?

26:22.079 --> 26:24.981
(AUDIENCE HOOTING)

26:26.415 --> 26:30.953
A handsome sheriff to tame
our buzzing bee, Mr. Wayne.

26:32.121 --> 26:35.358
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

26:37.694 --> 26:39.363
Congratulations, sir.

26:41.098 --> 26:42.998
You lucky devil, you.

26:43.000 --> 26:46.336
Any words for your
adoring and loving fans?

26:49.940 --> 26:51.039
(MICROPHONE GIVING FEEDBACK)

26:51.041 --> 26:51.943
Um...

26:53.243 --> 26:55.077
Thank you.

26:55.079 --> 26:56.980
Thank you all very much.

26:58.616 --> 27:00.051
It's, um...

27:02.252 --> 27:04.253
There you have it
ladies and gentlemen,

27:04.255 --> 27:08.290
your wonderful winners of
the champion costume contest.

27:08.292 --> 27:10.827
Bring on the apple-bobbing.

27:10.829 --> 27:12.462
Ready, Honey?

27:12.464 --> 27:15.533
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

27:16.534 --> 27:17.635
Ready, Mr. Wayne?

27:19.205 --> 27:22.108
(AUDIENCE BOOING)

27:24.977 --> 27:28.679
Now, on my mark we want to
see you bob for those apples

27:28.681 --> 27:31.050
like the crazy rotten
scoundrels you are.

27:32.584 --> 27:35.220
On your marks, get set,

27:35.222 --> 27:36.055
go.

27:36.889 --> 27:40.060
("GOSH" BY JAMIE XX)

27:45.098 --> 27:46.265
Oh my, oh my.

27:54.007 --> 27:56.575
And Honey is the first to bite.

27:57.611 --> 28:00.714
("GOSH" BY JAMIE XX)

28:09.991 --> 28:13.928
Bob away you debauched
Hallow's Eve reprobates.

28:14.828 --> 28:17.932
("GOSH" BY JAMIE XX)

28:21.536 --> 28:24.372
(AUDIENCE BOOING)

28:27.109 --> 28:30.179
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

28:31.612 --> 28:36.118
My, this is close ladies and
gentlemen, brutally close.

28:36.852 --> 28:39.454
("GOSH" BY JAMIE XX)

28:45.627 --> 28:46.827
Tensions all around my lovelies,

28:46.829 --> 28:49.398
you can slice it with a knife.

28:50.465 --> 28:53.535
("GOSH" BY JAMIE XX)

28:54.971 --> 28:58.908
Who will it be, who will
it be, I just don't know.

29:00.542 --> 29:03.178
[AUDIENCE] Three, two, one.

29:03.180 --> 29:06.981
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

29:06.983 --> 29:10.484
A magnificent comeback
by our darling, Honey.

29:10.486 --> 29:13.855
Three succulent apples apiece.

29:13.857 --> 29:17.425
What a civilized result
for you dirty, debauched,

29:17.427 --> 29:20.828
rotten, scandalous bunch.

29:20.830 --> 29:21.665
A draw.

29:23.133 --> 29:26.203
Your champions, Mr.
Wayne and Honey.

29:27.239 --> 29:30.307
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

29:31.675 --> 29:33.910
Oh, Inspector Shoerope,
what marvelous fun.

29:33.912 --> 29:35.178
[SHOEROPE] I'm an
apple bobbing fiend.

29:35.180 --> 29:37.980
What good, clean, fucking fun.

29:37.982 --> 29:40.049
You do know how to
throw quite some party.

29:40.051 --> 29:41.150
I do, don't I?

29:41.152 --> 29:42.085
A wicked time.

29:42.087 --> 29:43.319
Truly.

29:43.321 --> 29:44.120
I should like for to
always be in attendance.

29:44.122 --> 29:45.388
You can, you must.

29:45.390 --> 29:47.156
Forever more,
each and every year.

29:47.158 --> 29:48.858
I should like that very much.

29:48.860 --> 29:50.559
I feared you were going to
run away with those apples

29:50.561 --> 29:51.628
and leave me well in your wake.

29:51.630 --> 29:53.596
You made a spirited comeback.

29:53.598 --> 29:54.664
But you wouldn't
do that, would you?

29:54.666 --> 29:55.798
What?

29:55.800 --> 29:57.301
To me, on my
birthday of all days?

29:57.303 --> 29:58.137
Do what?

29:59.338 --> 30:01.437
Unless my sense
of human judgment

30:01.439 --> 30:03.874
has completely capitulated,

30:03.876 --> 30:06.845
then being a well-mannered
gentleman I've judged you to be,

30:08.281 --> 30:10.447
have you not always permitted
any competitive endeavor

30:10.449 --> 30:13.152
to be forfeited to those
withstanding their natal day?

30:14.519 --> 30:17.289
Why yes, I suppose I have.

30:17.291 --> 30:19.456
Forgive me, I was swept
away in the excitement

30:19.458 --> 30:21.027
seized by my competitive edge.

30:22.728 --> 30:25.095
The past is past.

30:25.097 --> 30:27.033
The future now holds
your redemption.

30:29.102 --> 30:30.170
To the future then.

30:34.675 --> 30:36.741
Well, hello there my lovelies.

30:36.743 --> 30:38.577
Mr. Conick, you
really must knock!

30:39.880 --> 30:41.280
Knock, knock.

30:41.282 --> 30:43.048
The apple bobbing
king and queen,

30:43.050 --> 30:45.284
as I live and as I breathe.

30:45.286 --> 30:46.419
Something like that.

30:46.421 --> 30:47.819
Oh and how thoroughly
well deserved.

30:47.821 --> 30:50.221
Truly, sincerely, thoroughly.

30:50.223 --> 30:53.192
I always think and hope and
pray that I might find myself

30:53.194 --> 30:57.166
upon that stage with a victory
to boast, but alas not yet.

30:58.233 --> 30:59.399
Not quite yet.

30:59.401 --> 31:01.033
Patience is a virtue.

31:01.035 --> 31:03.736
Indeed, one of these
years I shall reign

31:03.738 --> 31:05.339
supreme, I'm sure.

31:05.341 --> 31:06.839
Simply a law of averages.

31:06.841 --> 31:08.374
You have my vote.

31:08.376 --> 31:10.310
Oh yes, but Honey holds
the wand and Honey alone.

31:10.312 --> 31:12.680
The benefits of
being the hostess.

31:13.848 --> 31:15.582
Oh quite, and
too right as well.

31:15.584 --> 31:17.951
Home advantage and
all that, too right.

31:17.953 --> 31:18.952
Agreed.

31:18.954 --> 31:21.621
I am having an
absolute corker.

31:21.623 --> 31:23.358
Once again, nonetheless.

31:23.360 --> 31:26.893
Each and every year, the most
riotous of times guaranteed.

31:26.895 --> 31:29.397
It is a requirement I
return so that I remember

31:29.399 --> 31:34.070
how good a time I've had,
that's how good a time I have.

31:35.671 --> 31:39.173
(HONEY LAUGHING)

31:39.175 --> 31:40.276
Is that a crime?

31:41.811 --> 31:44.445
Oh gosh golly no, not
on my watch at least.

31:44.447 --> 31:47.081
Though I am rather liberal,
you do invite me back

31:47.083 --> 31:50.251
every year of course,
which is integral.

31:50.253 --> 31:51.054
I thank you.

31:53.157 --> 31:53.957
Oh bang!

31:54.991 --> 31:56.458
Double bang!

31:56.460 --> 31:57.361
Bang, bang!

32:01.499 --> 32:02.663
Either of you care for a tinker?

32:02.665 --> 32:03.699
Thank you but no.

32:03.701 --> 32:04.767
A little dabble?

32:04.769 --> 32:06.301
I haven't the constitution.

32:06.303 --> 32:07.568
A simple sniff?

32:07.570 --> 32:08.404
Not for me.

32:08.406 --> 32:09.239
Some booger sugar?

32:09.241 --> 32:10.240
Oh Mr. Conick, please.

32:10.242 --> 32:11.341
Damn shame.

32:11.343 --> 32:12.141
You'll find
everything you need here

32:12.143 --> 32:13.475
to spruce, up Mr. Wayne.

32:13.477 --> 32:15.912
Indeed it appears
well supplied.

32:15.914 --> 32:18.881
That apple bobbing is a
rotten messy business chap.

32:18.883 --> 32:20.249
Enjoy.

32:20.251 --> 32:21.887
Honey, shall we
peruse the party?

32:22.954 --> 32:24.620
I'll follow in a moment.

32:24.622 --> 32:26.289
Oh nonsense, away we go.

32:26.291 --> 32:31.127
Really, Mr. Conick,
I have hostess duties.

32:31.129 --> 32:32.797
Fine, as you wish.

32:34.833 --> 32:36.536
She's a stubborn
one, as you know.

32:38.537 --> 32:39.704
I'll be seeing you.

32:42.574 --> 32:43.606
Right, we have
a crime to solve.

32:43.608 --> 32:44.542
Of course.

32:44.544 --> 32:45.743
When you are refreshed,

32:45.745 --> 32:46.609
meet me in the piano
room post-haste.

32:46.611 --> 32:47.612
Certainly.

32:49.248 --> 32:50.982
Inspector Shoerope?

32:52.118 --> 32:53.651
Yes?

32:53.653 --> 32:54.885
I do so desperately hope
we can solve the mystery

32:54.887 --> 32:57.056
of the murder of my
husband only a year ago.

32:58.325 --> 32:59.125
We will.

33:00.494 --> 33:01.928
So that I may live in peace.

33:03.564 --> 33:04.398
You must.

33:05.865 --> 33:07.100
And embrace the future.

33:09.770 --> 33:11.171
Wholeheartedly.

33:16.877 --> 33:20.047
(JAZZY PIANO PLAYING)

33:34.963 --> 33:38.598
Mr. Wayne, my spick
and span champion.

33:38.600 --> 33:40.233
Interrupting something, am I?

33:40.235 --> 33:41.400
Whatever do you mean?

33:41.402 --> 33:43.972
I think you know,
what was that?

33:46.108 --> 33:47.374
You've endowed me
with a greater level

33:47.376 --> 33:49.476
of understanding than
I'm afraid I possess.

33:49.478 --> 33:53.213
What were you discussing
with Commissioner?

33:53.215 --> 33:56.215
My word, from where has
this petulance descended?

33:56.217 --> 33:58.852
In the name of the law,
it's imperative I be informed.

33:58.854 --> 33:59.685
[HONEY] You need a drink.

33:59.687 --> 34:01.188
I don't need a drink.

34:01.190 --> 34:02.456
Well, something's required
to calm you the fuck down.

34:02.458 --> 34:03.991
I need you to
divulge the truth.

34:03.993 --> 34:04.827
Excuse me?

34:07.263 --> 34:09.130
Commissioner ordered
I disbelieve any word

34:09.132 --> 34:10.500
that comes from your mouth.

34:11.699 --> 34:13.199
What?

34:13.202 --> 34:14.434
When?

34:14.436 --> 34:15.603
And in the ensuing
costume contest chaos

34:15.605 --> 34:17.306
and apple bobbing and what-not,

34:18.408 --> 34:19.909
I failed to uphold said order.

34:22.012 --> 34:23.478
How dare he.

34:23.480 --> 34:26.315
I am now reminded of
its importance, the truth.

34:27.552 --> 34:29.219
Commissioner and I

34:31.321 --> 34:33.621
intend to partake

34:33.623 --> 34:36.594
in a petite Hallow's Eve treat,

34:38.695 --> 34:41.163
and you caught us
fashioning the arrangements.

34:41.165 --> 34:42.598
Excuse me?

34:42.600 --> 34:45.001
We understandably desire
it to remain secret.

34:46.237 --> 34:49.138
He must have doubted my
ability to keep it so.

34:49.139 --> 34:50.272
You and the commissioner?

34:50.274 --> 34:51.641
It's merely a
physical act of pleasure

34:51.643 --> 34:52.475
we shall share, nothing more.

34:52.476 --> 34:54.076
Here's a married man!

34:54.078 --> 34:55.645
Mr. Wayne, how
insensitive of you!

34:55.647 --> 34:57.614
- Honey...
- I am a widow,

34:57.616 --> 34:58.981
a widow if you please.

34:58.983 --> 34:59.815
I didn't mean that.

34:59.817 --> 35:01.585
Consider my emotions.

35:01.587 --> 35:04.454
You've outdone even yourself
you heartless rascal.

35:04.456 --> 35:05.290
Please.

35:06.158 --> 35:07.758
Oh, why must I bear His cross?

35:08.759 --> 35:10.894
(PIANO KEYS BANGING)

35:10.896 --> 35:13.898
You have some nerve tormenting
a woman laden with tragedy.

35:18.705 --> 35:19.903
Stan down sir.

35:19.905 --> 35:22.073
Can't you see
Honey's vulnerable?

35:22.075 --> 35:23.710
Gently, Mr. Wayne.

35:25.210 --> 35:26.910
How dare you bring
tears upon her?

35:26.912 --> 35:28.379
You are entirely mistaken.

35:28.381 --> 35:30.717
She needs protection,
care and love, not a bully.

35:32.285 --> 35:36.387
That's very
impressive, both of you.

35:36.389 --> 35:39.658
Thank you, but I
am quite alright.

35:39.660 --> 35:41.360
Now relinquish
your lock at once.

35:41.362 --> 35:43.631
[SHOEROPE] With pleasure.

35:51.538 --> 35:53.639
You escaped me this
time young Tommy,

35:53.641 --> 35:56.075
but beware should you
begin to bully anew,

35:57.679 --> 35:59.313
I shall not hesitate.

36:01.048 --> 36:03.349
(MR. WERNER GIGGLING)

36:03.351 --> 36:04.419
Sit down, sir.

36:06.554 --> 36:07.388
Curse you.

36:19.634 --> 36:22.235
Frau Honey, it is a noble
tradition of the Fatherland

36:22.237 --> 36:24.404
to warm and delight
those in distress,

36:24.406 --> 36:27.074
particularly when the
damsel in question possesses

36:27.076 --> 36:29.044
such aesthetic charms as thee.

36:29.878 --> 36:31.110
Allow me?

36:31.112 --> 36:32.211
Oh, I'm touched
by your concern,

36:32.213 --> 36:34.116
but I really am quite fine.

36:35.850 --> 36:38.053
Nothing a wash of
absinthe won't flush away.

36:39.822 --> 36:42.356
Absolutely out of the
proverbial question.

36:42.358 --> 36:45.427
