won't you kind sir?

39:35.906 --> 39:39.176
(OLD WEST THEME MUSIC)

39:52.122 --> 39:54.256
You have some talking to do.

39:54.258 --> 39:55.390
Come again?

39:55.392 --> 39:57.360
Enough of your
mischief, Commissioner.

39:57.362 --> 39:59.529
Watch your mouth Shoerope,
remember who it is I am.

39:59.531 --> 40:00.997
I'm not so sure anymore.

40:00.999 --> 40:02.765
Another word, I'll rip
the guts from your garters.

40:02.767 --> 40:04.400
If anybody's doing any
any ripping, it's me.

40:04.402 --> 40:05.902
Come here!

40:05.904 --> 40:08.004
Stand still and receive
what's coming your way!

40:08.006 --> 40:10.273
You stand still
young bum, and receive

40:10.275 --> 40:11.641
what's coming your way!

40:11.643 --> 40:13.676
I'm merely a moral
messenger, but morality bites.

40:13.678 --> 40:16.947
Don't speak to me of
morals, stop moving!

40:16.949 --> 40:19.282
I shan't stop moving
until you admit all.

40:19.284 --> 40:20.216
Admit what?

40:20.218 --> 40:21.885
Your Hallow's Eve activities.

40:21.887 --> 40:24.253
My Hallow's Eve
activities, what of yours?

40:24.255 --> 40:25.087
Mine?

40:25.089 --> 40:26.289
Yes, yours, you cheat.

40:26.291 --> 40:28.091
You're the cheat,
she told me everything.

40:28.093 --> 40:28.960
What, who?

40:28.962 --> 40:30.527
Honey.

40:30.529 --> 40:32.998
Oh, stop this blasted
running at once.

40:34.768 --> 40:35.601
Fine.

40:38.904 --> 40:39.706
Commissioner.

40:40.807 --> 40:42.341
Commissioner sir, are you well?

40:43.542 --> 40:44.343
No, I'm not.

40:46.646 --> 40:49.481
I'm an aged man
who's still aging.

40:53.353 --> 40:54.220
Bring me my drink.

41:19.313 --> 41:22.949
(WHIMSICAL MUSIC)

41:22.951 --> 41:24.149
Commissioner!

41:24.151 --> 41:27.220
Shut your trap you
obnoxious little beaver,

41:27.222 --> 41:29.623
before I shut it for you.

41:29.625 --> 41:31.024
Get off me!

41:31.026 --> 41:32.027
That's it.

41:38.934 --> 41:43.939
There we are, much better.

41:49.411 --> 41:51.948
(BEES BUZZING)

41:54.249 --> 41:57.887
("FLIGHT OF THE BUMBLEBEE")

42:09.065 --> 42:11.565
It should have been me
victorious, but you came along,

42:11.567 --> 42:14.036
or should I say Mr. Wayne
came along, you rogue,

42:14.038 --> 42:15.270
- you libertine...
- Commissioner!

42:15.272 --> 42:16.974
Put my balls
back in your mouth!

42:19.442 --> 42:24.081
I know of your vulgar
elicit relations with Honey.

42:25.049 --> 42:25.883
What?

42:27.284 --> 42:29.551
You plan to partake in
a treat with one another

42:29.553 --> 42:30.686
this very Hallow's Eve.

42:30.688 --> 42:31.520
Treat?

42:31.522 --> 42:33.122
I think it despicable.

42:33.124 --> 42:36.425
Shoerope, I'm a happily
married man, how dare you!

42:36.427 --> 42:38.593
She told me of the
nasties you were whispering

42:38.595 --> 42:40.430
when I spied you both
earlier, don't play dumb.

42:40.432 --> 42:41.898
We were whispering
nothing of the sort.

42:41.900 --> 42:44.433
It was your fraudulent
victory I was vexing over.

42:44.435 --> 42:45.702
Excuse me?

42:45.704 --> 42:47.906
The costume you
fool, the costume!

42:49.107 --> 42:50.707
I was informing Honey
of my utter discontent

42:50.709 --> 42:52.608
that annually I attend
this shambolic shindig,

42:52.610 --> 42:54.477
having spent the many
preceding months contemplating

42:54.479 --> 42:56.312
and planning and
deliberating with my dear,

42:56.314 --> 42:58.782
dear wife as to what costumes
we shall be sporting,

42:58.784 --> 43:01.954
and annually we are
left empty handed.

43:02.854 --> 43:04.121
What?

43:04.123 --> 43:05.825
We even practiced the
apple-bobbing together.

43:07.459 --> 43:08.493
Blast you rotten!

43:10.730 --> 43:11.962
Practice?

43:11.964 --> 43:14.031
My wife's marvelous at
grabbing those fruits.

43:14.033 --> 43:16.901
She'll be wonderful when
her time finally comes.

43:16.903 --> 43:18.270
Oh, get up you imbecile.

43:20.005 --> 43:24.477
A nomination would suffice,
alas not even a sniff.

43:28.715 --> 43:31.883
But Honey told me of your
physical act of pleasure.

43:31.885 --> 43:33.587
Physical pleasure?

43:34.955 --> 43:37.958
There is no pleasure.

43:40.460 --> 43:42.061
So,

43:42.063 --> 43:43.328
so Honey was...

43:43.330 --> 43:44.562
Did I not order you
to disbelieve any word

43:44.564 --> 43:46.331
that comes from
her insane mouth?

43:46.333 --> 43:47.166
Yes Commissioner, you did.

43:47.168 --> 43:48.002
Heed my order.

43:49.269 --> 43:51.672
Then why did you suspiciously
run as I approached?

43:54.175 --> 43:55.342
Frustration.

43:56.476 --> 43:57.478
Envy.

43:58.746 --> 43:59.680
Shame.

44:01.282 --> 44:04.951
Disappointment in the
heat of the moment.

44:04.953 --> 44:08.489
Oh, how shall I
face my sugarplum?

44:11.492 --> 44:12.993
I'm a winner by definition.

44:12.995 --> 44:16.532
I wanted to win so dearly
this year of all years.

44:17.833 --> 44:19.065
You could have faced me?

44:19.067 --> 44:20.566
Oh, no I couldn't,
I had to run and hide

44:20.568 --> 44:23.872
in this very room and play
billiards, the coward I am.

44:26.642 --> 44:27.944
I'm appalling.

44:31.680 --> 44:34.682
I'm quite amazing at billiards
though, I never lose.

44:34.684 --> 44:37.619
How victories feed the spirit
and replenish the soul.

44:39.190 --> 44:41.157
So there is no...

44:42.258 --> 44:43.090
Nothing.

44:43.092 --> 44:44.558
No of course not.

44:44.560 --> 44:48.798
The only holes I shall fill
are on this here table.

44:51.135 --> 44:55.306
(MUSIC PLAYING IN
THE BACKGROUND)

44:57.040 --> 44:59.276
The cruel spectrum of life.

45:01.879 --> 45:02.712
Honey,

45:03.614 --> 45:07.850
the victor, year in, year out,

45:07.852 --> 45:11.087
and I, the perpetual loser.

45:11.089 --> 45:12.988
Have you considered
Commissioner,

45:12.990 --> 45:14.456
the code of etiquette
that stipulates

45:14.458 --> 45:16.993
those withstanding their natal
day shall reign victorious

45:16.995 --> 45:18.760
throughout any
competitive endeavor?

45:18.762 --> 45:19.595
Natal day?

45:19.597 --> 45:20.429
Honey's birthday.

45:20.431 --> 45:21.464
Who told you that?

45:21.466 --> 45:22.765
- Honey.
- My order, Shoerope.

45:22.767 --> 45:24.000
What?

45:24.002 --> 45:25.735
Heed my bloody order,
it's not her birthday!

45:25.737 --> 45:27.204
What?

45:27.206 --> 45:28.005
Not a syllable uttered from
her lips should land true

45:28.007 --> 45:30.273
upon your naive ears.

45:30.275 --> 45:31.441
Commissioner I feel awfully...

45:31.443 --> 45:32.976
Whatever am I
going to do with you?

45:32.978 --> 45:34.178
Awfully, slight in
this very moment...

45:34.180 --> 45:36.479
Shoerope, shoerope,
what's the matter?

45:36.481 --> 45:37.447
Commissioner you'll
have to excuse me.

45:37.449 --> 45:38.383
Shoerope?

45:39.852 --> 45:41.285
Shoerope?

45:41.287 --> 45:44.623
(DRAMATIC THEME MUSIC)

45:48.961 --> 45:49.795
Shoerope!

45:51.597 --> 45:52.431
Shoerope!

45:53.633 --> 45:54.467
Shoerope!

45:56.035 --> 45:56.869
Shoerope!

45:57.871 --> 46:00.374
For the sake of God, Shoerope!

46:01.507 --> 46:04.745
(DRAMATIC THEME MUSIC)

46:21.696 --> 46:24.265
(SERENE MUSIC)

46:38.745 --> 46:41.250
(SOFT MUSIC)

46:51.894 --> 46:53.629
Inspector Shoerope?

46:58.534 --> 47:00.102
Inspector Shoerope?

47:06.343 --> 47:07.910
Inspector Shoerope?

47:10.512 --> 47:11.948
Wake up, darling.

47:14.284 --> 47:15.984
There you are.

47:15.986 --> 47:16.820
Honey.

47:20.023 --> 47:21.789
Honey is that you?

47:21.791 --> 47:22.959
Yours truly.

47:24.494 --> 47:25.729
How are you feeling?

47:28.199 --> 47:29.100
I'm feeling very

47:30.934 --> 47:33.235
heavy, actually.

47:33.237 --> 47:37.039
Of course you are,
you took quite a tumble.

47:37.041 --> 47:37.841
Yes.

47:39.378 --> 47:40.909
Yes, I suppose I did.

47:40.911 --> 47:43.912
You really must endeavor to
match every glass of liquor

47:43.914 --> 47:46.617
with a dash of fresh air or

47:47.818 --> 47:49.820
splash of water
at the very least.

47:51.189 --> 47:52.921
[SHOEROPE] Right.

47:52.923 --> 47:56.558
Have a sip on this,
there's a drop of my

47:56.560 --> 47:59.297
homemade honey mixed within,
you'll feel right as rain.

48:05.871 --> 48:06.705
Mmm.

48:08.373 --> 48:09.873
Delicious.

48:09.875 --> 48:11.308
You keep your own bees?

48:11.310 --> 48:14.344
In memory of my
deceased husband, you see.

48:14.346 --> 48:16.380
It wasn't just me he kept.

48:16.382 --> 48:19.017
He was a bee enthusiast
of nearly half a century.

48:21.187 --> 48:23.120
They make wonderful companions.

48:23.122 --> 48:24.123
It would taste so.

48:26.325 --> 48:28.828
(SOFT MUSIC)

48:34.767 --> 48:35.601
Honey.

48:38.704 --> 48:42.174
I confronted Commissioner
regarding the physical act

48:42.176 --> 48:43.743
of pleasure between you and he.

48:44.610 --> 48:45.446
And?

48:46.747 --> 48:48.415
It would seem
you've misled me.

48:52.487 --> 48:56.054
Have I not welcomed you
into my home with grace?

48:56.056 --> 48:56.957
You have.

48:58.259 --> 48:59.093
And,

49:01.395 --> 49:03.996
are you not in my employment?

49:03.998 --> 49:06.934
You did call me hither, which
plants me in your service.

49:08.303 --> 49:09.669
And have I not, on
a more personal note,

49:09.671 --> 49:10.705
been most hospitable?

49:12.407 --> 49:14.042
I would again, have to agree.

49:15.777 --> 49:18.246
Then why do you doubt
my word against his?

49:20.515 --> 49:21.448
He is Commissioner.

49:21.450 --> 49:23.683
And a married man to boot.

49:23.685 --> 49:25.488
He's established
his faithfulness.

49:28.324 --> 49:31.258
Commissioner or no, he
has thus far proven impotent

49:31.260 --> 49:33.827
in his lame attempts to
solve the despicable crime

49:33.829 --> 49:36.130
of the murder of my husband.

49:36.132 --> 49:37.932
It's an ongoing investigation.

49:39.336 --> 49:42.669
So the killer is at
large, in this very house,

49:42.671 --> 49:45.240
at this very exact
precise moment!

49:45.242 --> 49:46.474
You have my sympathy.

49:46.476 --> 49:48.278
I don't want your
fucking sympathy!

49:49.678 --> 49:51.248
I want justice.

49:56.952 --> 49:58.720
He did further make
me aware that today

49:58.722 --> 50:00.991
is not in fact your birthday.

50:03.127 --> 50:04.659
Inspector Shoerope.

50:04.661 --> 50:07.328
It appears all the cats
are rather out of the bag.

50:07.330 --> 50:09.365
You apparently think
that every word I speak

50:09.367 --> 50:11.001
is without an ounce of truth.

50:13.604 --> 50:14.771
Not even a syllable?

50:16.040 --> 50:18.675
That is exactly what I think.

50:22.146 --> 50:22.980
You may leave.

50:24.448 --> 50:26.881
It is peculiar no fellow
reveler has spoken a word

50:26.883 --> 50:28.418
of your birthday.

50:28.420 --> 50:30.753
All I know of it is what you
and only you have mentioned.

50:30.755 --> 50:32.754
I insist you depart.

50:32.756 --> 50:35.225
Don't let anger
veil the truth.

50:35.227 --> 50:36.992
I urge you to understand
my predicament

50:36.994 --> 50:39.229
and the subsequent conclusion
to which it has led me.

50:39.231 --> 50:41.965
It is smart indeed to
ask for understanding

50:41.967 --> 50:43.402
when he who asks has nil.

50:44.936 --> 50:47.704
I willingly informed you today
was my natal day because,

50:47.706 --> 50:48.706
well because...

50:50.175 --> 50:52.679
I took an immediate liking
to you, Inspector Shoerope.

50:54.413 --> 50:55.914
A liking of the aesthetic sort.

50:59.885 --> 51:02.955
And you are alone in your
awareness of it being so,

51:03.957 --> 51:05.258
for reasons of vanity.

51:11.731 --> 51:15.902
If it is a crime for
a woman to lament

51:16.869 --> 51:18.171
the passing of time,

51:25.512 --> 51:27.448
the betrayal of her beauty,

51:32.919 --> 51:36.023
the dawning of old
age and ultimately,

51:37.391 --> 51:38.758
the tidings of death,

51:40.395 --> 51:42.796
then consider me a criminal
in the first degree.

51:46.234 --> 51:48.134
And if these tears
are interpreted by you

51:48.136 --> 51:49.571
as the crocodile variety,

51:50.739 --> 51:53.473
then I command you
cast your cynical eye

51:53.475 --> 51:55.410
on the birth certificate
I keep framed

51:56.611 --> 51:58.445
next to the marriage
certificate of me

51:58.447 --> 52:01.414
and my dear deceased husband
on the side of the bed

52:01.416 --> 52:03.119
that he would be inhabiting.

52:05.920 --> 52:10.359
If it weren't for the minor
detail of his brutal murder

52:11.494 --> 52:13.895
in this very home
only a year ago today.

52:21.170 --> 52:22.671
Here.

52:22.673 --> 52:25.474
I sincerely hope that
you enjoy the read.

52:27.843 --> 52:31.080
(SOFT DRAMATIC THEME)

52:41.892 --> 52:42.726
Bugger.

52:43.660 --> 52:47.162
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

52:47.164 --> 52:48.430
Tatiana!

52:48.432 --> 52:51.933
I'm looking for Honey,
have you seen her?

52:51.935 --> 52:52.704
Honey, Honey!

52:59.577 --> 53:02.814
(PUNCHING AND GRUNTING)

53:07.385 --> 53:09.286
[COMMISSIONER] I'm
positive it's the exact one.

53:09.288 --> 53:10.754
[MR. CONICK] Agreed.

53:10.756 --> 53:12.622
[MR. WERNER] The very moment
he stepped foot on stage,

53:12.624 --> 53:13.856
I too was convinced.

53:13.858 --> 53:15.024
(SHOEROPE COUGHING)

53:15.026 --> 53:16.360
[MR. CONICK] Quick,
he's coming to.

53:16.362 --> 53:17.296
Look busy, chaps.

53:26.237 --> 53:28.507
(COUGHING)

53:39.085 --> 53:40.186
Mr. Conick.

53:42.522 --> 53:43.456
Mr. Werner.

53:46.993 --> 53:47.924
Commissioner.

53:47.926 --> 53:49.227
Rise and shine, Shoerope.

53:49.229 --> 53:50.060
Whatever's going on?

53:50.062 --> 53:50.994
We're in the kitchen.

53:50.996 --> 53:54.300
Yes, yes, I see that.

53:55.769 --> 53:56.935
Why am I tied up?

53:58.339 --> 53:59.937
Gentlemen, is this a game?

53:59.939 --> 54:02.740
You're in deep, Shoerope.

54:02.742 --> 54:05.744
She likes you, a mystery
as to why but it is so.

54:05.746 --> 54:06.645
What, who?

54:06.647 --> 54:07.448
Honey.

54:09.183 --> 54:10.382
And what of it?

54:10.384 --> 54:12.317
She spreads her
affection rather thin.

54:12.319 --> 54:15.588
With affection comes
a weakness, trust.

54:15.590 --> 54:17.189
Trust?

54:17.191 --> 54:18.792
Trust.

54:18.794 --> 54:19.992
We want you to do
something for us,

54:19.994 --> 54:22.262
something vital for our cause.

54:22.264 --> 54:24.129
Kidnapping and then
roping me to a chair

54:24.131 --> 54:26.165
is a curious approach
when asking a favor.

54:26.167 --> 54:29.135
I rather enjoyed roping a
certain Inspector Shoerope.

54:29.137 --> 54:31.406
(LAUGHING)

54:33.241 --> 54:36.176
It is no favor and you
will be heavily rewarded.

54:36.178 --> 54:37.644
Financially.

54:37.646 --> 54:40.313
Get Honey into this kitchen
before the evening is out.

54:40.315 --> 54:41.548
Excuse me?

54:41.550 --> 54:43.884
Bring her in, that's
it, and that's all.

54:43.886 --> 54:45.486
(LAUGHING)

54:45.488 --> 54:49.022
Forgive my hesitation gentlemen
but this is most suspicious.

54:49.024 --> 54:50.290
Oh, just do it.

54:50.292 --> 54:51.694
Are you barmy?

54:54.062 --> 54:54.897
Wait.

54:56.398 --> 54:57.400
The kitchen.

55:00.903 --> 55:02.238
Wait, it can't really be.

55:05.441 --> 55:06.844
Honey's husband, a year ago?

55:09.146 --> 55:10.345
Eureka.

55:10.347 --> 55:12.248
You brutes, you murderers!

55:13.282 --> 55:14.448
Commissioner, you traitor!

55:14.450 --> 55:15.852
It's business, Shoerope.

55:15.854 --> 55:18.720
Congratulations,
and welcome aboard.

55:18.722 --> 55:20.655
Business my left
foot, you're criminals.

55:20.657 --> 55:23.658
We are all serving
the great Mein Fuhrer

55:23.660 --> 55:26.628
and you too are now under
his splendid command.

55:26.630 --> 55:28.464
You're under arrest.

55:28.466 --> 55:30.131
(CHUCKLING)

55:30.133 --> 55:31.566
Commissioner it's not
too late, get them!

55:31.568 --> 55:34.002
The only one getting
got is Honey, tonight,

55:34.004 --> 55:35.170
in this very room.

55:35.172 --> 55:36.772
Why are you
doing such a thing?

55:36.774 --> 55:38.843
Money, Inspector Shoerope.

55:39.912 --> 55:41.310
You animals.

55:41.312 --> 55:42.745
We dispatched of
Honey's husband a year ago

55:42.747 --> 55:46.148
intending for to obtain
this marvelous property.

55:46.150 --> 55:48.751
The old fool wouldn't
sell, you see,

55:48.753 --> 55:50.253
but upon the owner's death,

55:50.255 --> 55:54.590
the title of the estate
rightfully returns to my family.

55:54.592 --> 55:57.694
I then can purchase
it from the Conicks

55:57.696 --> 55:59.596
on behalf of Mein Fuhrer.

55:59.598 --> 56:02.668
An idyllic rural stronghold.

56:04.069 --> 56:08.271
And after our mighty German
invasion of your British Isles,

56:08.273 --> 56:10.675
this home will
serve as our perfect

56:10.677 --> 56:12.309
United Kingdom headquarters.

56:12.311 --> 56:13.744
Invasion?

56:13.746 --> 56:17.515
A great war is looming,
Inspector Shoerope.

56:17.517 --> 56:19.449
Long live the Fatherland, yah?

56:19.451 --> 56:20.952
(LAUGHING)

56:20.954 --> 56:22.887
This is insanity.

56:22.889 --> 56:25.124
(LAUGHING)

56:26.860 --> 56:29.796
An act of complete
sanity, I assure you.

56:30.931 --> 56:32.463
(STOMPING CANE TO THE GROUND)

56:32.465 --> 56:36.601
Only that Honey's husband,
the shrewd nitwit he was,

56:36.603 --> 56:41.006
secretly registered the title
of the estate in Honey's name,

56:41.008 --> 56:45.110
and our perfectly
orchestrated murder a year ago

56:45.112 --> 56:46.247
came to nothing.

56:49.149 --> 56:51.183
There are many estates
like it, purchase another.

56:51.185 --> 56:53.252
This is the finest
property in England.

56:53.254 --> 56:55.421
You won't find any better.

56:55.423 --> 56:57.158
And Mein Fuhrer
only wants the best.

56:59.260 --> 57:03.563
And Commissioner, you've
been an accomplice all along,

57:03.565 --> 57:07.700
perverting the course of justice
as only a commissioner can?

57:07.702 --> 57:10.305
A man is capable of
anything for the right figure,

57:12.307 --> 57:14.340
as you'll soon discover.

57:14.342 --> 57:16.743
How can you live
with yourself?

57:16.745 --> 57:18.745
The Germans are brewing
a second world war

57:18.747 --> 57:21.014
and you're in aid in the
inevitable demise of our country,

57:21.016 --> 57:22.449
if not the entire globe.

57:22.451 --> 57:24.852
War is an economic
tool and I mean for to be

57:24.854 --> 57:26.121
a key craftsman.

57:29.993 --> 57:30.994
I won't do it.

57:33.162 --> 57:34.829
Out of the question.

57:34.831 --> 57:35.963
(MR. WERNER SIGHING)

57:35.965 --> 57:37.498
There is no question.

57:37.500 --> 57:38.433
None at all.

57:39.636 --> 57:42.803
You haven't the
liberty of choice.

57:42.805 --> 57:46.142
(KNOCKING AT THE DOOR)

58:15.141 --> 58:18.708
When I was a young
girl doing the learning

58:18.710 --> 58:22.847
of the birds and of the
bees, I had to educate a boy,

58:23.815 --> 58:24.649
Jean Paul.

58:25.717 --> 58:28.054
How I loved Jean Paul.

58:29.387 --> 58:32.488
I gave him everything.

58:32.490 --> 58:37.495
I gave him all my hopes and all
my smiles and all my dreams.

58:38.863 --> 58:42.434
And he in return gave
me everything, too.

58:43.602 --> 58:46.870
A summer of passion,

58:46.872 --> 58:48.507
beautiful passion.

58:51.611 --> 58:55.746
When the weather fell cold
and the autumn arrived,

58:55.748 --> 58:58.750
I traveled to Paris,
avec my darling mother,

58:58.752 --> 59:00.919
to purchase a jacket.

59:00.921 --> 59:03.557
I was feeling quite chilly
in the farm, you see.

59:04.991 --> 59:08.459
The first jacket I tried on
fitted perfectly, my body.

59:08.461 --> 59:11.431
It was tight on the waist and
smooth on my derrière, voila!

59:13.934 --> 59:16.869
When we returned home
some hours early,

59:16.871 --> 59:19.704
see Jean Paul wasn't really
used to seeing me wear

59:19.706 --> 59:21.340
a lot of clothes.

59:21.342 --> 59:25.144
So I ran to his house, wearing
the jacket I want him to see

59:25.146 --> 59:27.313
because it looks so pretty.

59:27.315 --> 59:32.319
I climb the stairs, I tiptoe
to the door of his bedroom

59:33.387 --> 59:36.424
and I pushed it slowly open.

59:37.658 --> 59:39.561
And more open,

59:41.262 --> 59:43.564
and more open,

59:45.267 --> 59:47.002
and there was my JP.

59:49.104 --> 59:53.942
And just like you, at this
moment, he was in the ropes,

59:55.343 --> 59:59.281
and just like you, at this
moment, he was with three men.

01:00:00.682 --> 01:00:04.386
But naked was my JP
and naked was them all.

01:00:07.589 --> 01:00:09.626
So before you become naked,

01:00:12.128 --> 01:00:15.932
I'll say what I
said to my dear JP,

01:00:17.400 --> 01:00:18.968
what is wrong with women?

01:00:25.775 --> 01:00:28.679
(WHIMSICAL MUSIC)

01:00:32.049 --> 01:00:34.418
Thank you for the
milk, au revoir.

01:00:40.825 --> 01:00:42.124
Bang!

01:00:42.126 --> 01:00:43.158
(MR. WERNER SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:00:43.160 --> 01:00:45.762
What a perfect
imbecile was JP.

01:00:45.764 --> 01:00:49.498
Don't be an imbecile
too, Shoerope.

01:00:49.500 --> 01:00:50.568
Get Honey

01:00:52.070 --> 01:00:53.271
into this kitchen.

01:00:55.973 --> 01:01:00.912
♪ It had to be you

01:01:02.580 --> 01:01:07.586
♪ It had to be you

01:01:09.521 --> 01:01:13.489
♪ I wandered around

01:01:13.491 --> 01:01:16.994
♪ And finally found

01:01:16.996 --> 01:01:22.001
♪ That somebody who

01:01:22.902 --> 01:01:27.473
♪ Could make me be true

01:01:28.808 --> 01:01:33.814
♪ Could make me feel blue

01:01:35.681 --> 01:01:39.751
♪ And even be glad

01:01:39.753 --> 01:01:43.188
♪ Just to be sad

01:01:43.190 --> 01:01:48.195
♪ Thinking of you

01:01:49.129 --> 01:01:53.500
♪ Some others I've seen

01:01:54.935 --> 01:01:57.270
♪ Might never be mean

01:01:57.272 --> 01:02:00.805
I'm fulled to the brim
with apologies, Honey.

01:02:00.807 --> 01:02:02.607
Can you forgive me?

01:02:02.609 --> 01:02:05.477
Any woman worth her
salt can find forgiveness

01:02:05.479 --> 01:02:06.314
in her heart.

01:02:08.082 --> 01:02:11.486
And I wish you the
happiest of birthdays.

01:02:13.221 --> 01:02:16.390
In fact I should very much
like to give you a gift.

01:02:16.392 --> 01:02:17.357
How exciting.

01:02:17.359 --> 01:02:18.624
A most treasured present.

01:02:18.626 --> 01:02:19.992
Go on.

01:02:19.994 --> 01:02:23.596
Well, it appears
a considerably

01:02:23.598 --> 01:02:25.934
scandalous scent still lingers.

01:02:28.037 --> 01:02:29.502
Yes.

01:02:29.504 --> 01:02:33.440
The trailing of said scent
has led me to one place.

01:02:33.442 --> 01:02:34.277
Where's that?

01:02:35.345 --> 01:02:36.178
The kitchen.

01:02:39.115 --> 01:02:41.049
I have previously informed
you that the murder took place

01:02:41.051 --> 01:02:42.616
in that very room, have I not?

01:02:42.618 --> 01:02:43.984
You have.

01:02:43.986 --> 01:02:46.054
And so it is my conclusion
that the kitchen

01:02:46.056 --> 01:02:49.523
is where I must be at the precise
moment of the anniversary

01:02:49.525 --> 01:02:50.726
of your husband's death.

01:02:54.596 --> 01:02:57.767
You must do whatever is
required to solve the crime,

01:02:59.102 --> 01:03:01.235
the success of which
would without doubt be

01:03:01.237 --> 01:03:02.571
a thrilling gift to unwrap.

01:03:04.208 --> 01:03:06.375
If I'm right in assuming
it's of that nature?

01:03:06.377 --> 01:03:07.210
Of course.

01:03:08.545 --> 01:03:10.715
The bestowing excites
me to my very core.

01:03:13.850 --> 01:03:17.989
This gift however does
necessitate your involvement.

01:03:19.589 --> 01:03:23.462
Aside from my receiving it,
I can't fathom what you mean.

01:03:24.595 --> 01:03:25.429
I should like,

01:03:27.598 --> 01:03:29.232
you see,

01:03:29.234 --> 01:03:30.801
for you to accompany me.

01:03:34.373 --> 01:03:35.207
Excuse me?

01:03:36.640 --> 01:03:40.343
This is the final piece
of the puzzle, and you,

01:03:40.345 --> 01:03:42.611
the facilitator of the picture
we're piecing together,

01:03:42.613 --> 01:03:46.417
need to be present upon
placing that defining segment.

01:03:46.419 --> 01:03:47.385
Release me.

01:03:47.387 --> 01:03:48.220
Honey.

01:03:49.988 --> 01:03:52.925
I refuse to entertain
such a gross idea.

01:03:55.127 --> 01:03:58.364
(SOFT DRAMATIC THEME)

01:04:01.767 --> 01:04:02.567
Honey!

01:04:03.536 --> 01:04:04.869
Allow me to explain.

01:04:04.871 --> 01:04:06.370
Remove your presumptuous
hands from me.

01:04:06.372 --> 01:04:08.472
The very truly last thing
anyone would have me do

01:04:08.474 --> 01:04:11.476
in this fucking world is
precisely what you requested.

01:04:11.478 --> 01:04:13.478
Wild horses couldn't
drag me near.

01:04:13.480 --> 01:04:14.879
In matters solving
a murder mystery,

01:04:14.881 --> 01:04:16.381
one must go to extreme lengths.

01:04:16.383 --> 01:04:17.815
Of that I'm not aware,
look around at my efforts.

01:04:17.817 --> 01:04:19.683
[SHOEROPE] So don't jeopardize
reaping their rewards.

01:04:19.685 --> 01:04:20.918
Honey, look at me.

01:04:20.920 --> 01:04:22.220
I refuse to share
your foolhardy glance.

01:04:22.222 --> 01:04:23.789
Trust my
professional judgment.

01:04:23.791 --> 01:04:26.525
My trust in you
is on tenterhooks.

01:04:26.527 --> 01:04:28.494
You've doubted numerous
pieces of information

01:04:28.496 --> 01:04:29.928
I've offered you,

01:04:29.930 --> 01:04:31.129
including the intimate
details of my date of birth.

01:04:31.131 --> 01:04:32.596
I can only apologize.

01:04:32.598 --> 01:04:33.901
Oh, fuck your apology!

01:04:37.805 --> 01:04:41.409
(THUNDER CRACKLING SOFTLY)

01:04:51.119 --> 01:04:52.720
What is it you would have me do?

01:04:54.322 --> 01:04:56.189
It's not uncommon for
the murderer to revisit

01:04:56.191 --> 01:04:57.657
the scene of their crime.

01:04:57.659 --> 01:04:59.226
I shall murder the murderer
myself if that's the case.

01:04:59.228 --> 01:05:01.629
Allow me to take charge
of their comeuppance.

01:05:03.532 --> 01:05:05.600
Then my contribution is what?

01:05:08.136 --> 01:05:12.638
I believe the criminal may
have set their sights upon you.

01:05:12.640 --> 01:05:14.141
Me?

01:05:14.143 --> 01:05:15.711
You're directly in their
cross-hairs, I believe.

01:05:17.079 --> 01:05:19.146
So I'm your fucking bait.

01:05:19.148 --> 01:05:20.082
Do you trust me?

01:05:21.351 --> 01:05:22.185
Do you?

01:05:23.353 --> 01:05:25.219
If we neglect this
final ray of light

01:05:25.221 --> 01:05:27.222
that shines upon the mystery,

01:05:27.224 --> 01:05:29.292
the truth may forever
remain in the dark.

01:05:32.496 --> 01:05:34.129
I shall make sure no
ill will come of it,

01:05:34.131 --> 01:05:35.899
it will pass as a
fleeting moment.

01:05:38.368 --> 01:05:39.203
By my side?

01:05:40.338 --> 01:05:42.372
With proximity we
share right this second.

01:05:46.477 --> 01:05:47.311
Very well.

01:05:53.817 --> 01:05:56.820
(TENSE THEME MUSIC)

01:05:57.922 --> 01:05:59.822
(MR. CONICK SHOUTING)

01:05:59.824 --> 01:06:01.723
No, no, no you fool!

01:06:01.725 --> 01:06:02.657
(MR. WERNER SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:06:02.659 --> 01:06:03.493
Disgrace to the Fatherland!

01:06:03.495 --> 01:06:04.327
Too much?

01:06:04.329 --> 01:06:05.562
We are not pirates!

01:06:05.564 --> 01:06:06.762
You're meant to
stab the woman,

01:06:06.764 --> 01:06:08.696
not scare her like a schoolboy!

01:06:08.698 --> 01:06:11.934
Simply jump in and quietly
and quickly, stick it in.

01:06:11.936 --> 01:06:12.770
Try again.

01:06:13.771 --> 01:06:15.004
Why must it be me?

01:06:15.006 --> 01:06:16.473
I'm certainly not
doing your dirty work.

01:06:16.475 --> 01:06:19.276
I had my fun last year,
taking a life is good for you,

01:06:19.278 --> 01:06:22.179
it'll give you a real
zest for your own.

01:06:22.181 --> 01:06:24.581
Yah, one more time.

01:06:24.583 --> 01:06:26.749
Fine, tell me when.

01:06:26.751 --> 01:06:28.952
[COMMISSIONER]
The door is opening,

01:06:28.954 --> 01:06:31.223
she take two steps forward.

01:06:33.326 --> 01:06:34.758
And now!

01:06:34.760 --> 01:06:35.692
Yah!

01:06:35.694 --> 01:06:36.726
Yah, there you go, very good.

01:06:36.728 --> 01:06:37.928
[COMMISSIONER] Huzzah.

01:06:37.930 --> 01:06:39.163
What if it's him
on this side instead?

01:06:39.165 --> 01:06:40.431
He'll go down easy,
then move on to her.

01:06:40.433 --> 01:06:42.699
I have no respect for
Shoerope's wellbeing.

01:06:42.701 --> 01:06:44.202
Good.

01:06:44.204 --> 01:06:47.305
Switch off the lights and
let's assume positions.

01:06:47.307 --> 01:06:50.874
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

01:06:50.876 --> 01:06:52.477
[MR. WERNER] Positions.

01:06:52.479 --> 01:06:54.981
(CAPER MUSIC)

01:07:07.561 --> 01:07:08.395
Coo-ey?

01:07:10.097 --> 01:07:10.931
Hello?

01:07:14.168 --> 01:07:16.304
Mr. Conick are you in here?

01:07:19.440 --> 01:07:20.772
Mr. Conick?

01:07:20.774 --> 01:07:21.708
[MR. CONICK] Tatiana!

01:07:21.710 --> 01:07:23.243
Oh, I knew it, you rascal you.

01:07:23.245 --> 01:07:25.712
What is she doing?

01:07:25.714 --> 01:07:28.181
Hello gentlemen,
what a lovely surprise.

01:07:28.183 --> 01:07:29.415
- Get her out.
- Right away!

01:07:29.417 --> 01:07:30.350
Excuse me?

01:07:30.352 --> 01:07:31.584
Tatiana you must leave.

01:07:31.586 --> 01:07:33.487
I am no dog to
be ordered around.

01:07:33.489 --> 01:07:34.688
Bugger off!

01:07:34.690 --> 01:07:36.389
I'm not going anywhere
thank you very much,

01:07:36.391 --> 01:07:38.691
and I'm certainly not leaving
until I get an apology

01:07:38.693 --> 01:07:40.994
for such impolite and
unwelcoming behavior.

01:07:40.996 --> 01:07:44.397
You are not welcome,
hence the behavior, out!

01:07:44.399 --> 01:07:47.767
This is the 20th century
sir, show some respect.

01:07:47.769 --> 01:07:50.471
I'll find you later,
Tatiana you must leave.

01:07:50.473 --> 01:07:52.506
